:INFO
The Novel I Needed to Read Twice Before I Could Leave It
I finished Normal People at around midnight on a Tuesday and lay awake for an \
hour thinking about Connell and Marianne and all the things they never quite \
managed to say. By Wednesday morning I had turned back to page one. Sally Rooney \
writes about the gap between what two people feel and what they actually say in \
a way that makes ordinary conversation feel like a failure of nerve on every page.

